social_posts.post_text: Behind the scenes! In addition to checking progress, I love going to projects at different times of day, because I get to see the sun glisten through the windows… pure heaven. Lighting is so important in a home, especially at these golden hours ✨

Looking back through my camera roll and reminiscing on this trip! I decided it’s probably time to share some of my favorites 🤍

Greece and Jerusalem have some of the most beautiful architecture in the world which is always an inspiration. I love adding elements of my travels into my designs!
our team is growing… 👼🏼🖤 #pregnant #alikadesign #crandallcorner #grateful @lakenluntphotography @gatherstudioutah

🪑 @building_brookline formal dining —the room everyone loved in the Parade of Homes!

Need help decorating your Christmas tree this year? This guide gives you five tips on how to spruce up your tree and be ready for the holidays! 🎄

Do you need extra space for visiting grandkids? This lovely Mother In Law Suite includes a pullout bed for all the littles running around! I love how this room exhibits warmth from the light coming in the windows and the handmade Turkish rug is so special! 🤍🤍🤍 #lakerushhill

Need inspiration when it comes to decorating bathrooms? This room can be so hard to find pieces for, but all it needs are simple and unique touches to make it a place of refuge in the home ✨

Which bathroom is your favorite? Let me know! 🤎

#EuropeanMountain I think it is finally time to show this dreamy kitchen and dining area... anyone else in love? 🤎 My favorite part of this build was incorporating natural light with earthy green and brown tones. This calming space is a perfect setup for family and friends to all be together!

We’ve been working on a special secret project! We are finishing up those last few details that bring it all together ✨ we can’t wait to show you 🎄🎁

A day in the life! Every day looks so different (which is one of many reasons I love what I do!) but this is what a typical Monday - Wednesday looks like for us at Alika Design 🏠❄️ we block these days out for all meetings, appointments, on site visits, etc! Thursday & Friday are our office days 🖥️ one of the greatest lessons I’ve learned this year (from my wise, amazing husband) is that I get to set my non negotiable’s, choose when I respond, decide how to delegate, know when my family needs me and when I need me. Learning these things has made me a much better designer, mother, wife, employer + business owner! 🤍

One way to elevate a room: add small touches and details! Both are important, and make a room unique and special in every way 🤍

One tip that I always recommend to anyone designing a home is to add greenery in rooms to bring earthy tones and life, even if it is a fake plant 😋. Adding greenery helps to elevate the room with these touches, big or small! In most of my feed, you can see at least some type of greenery in most rooms. I absolutely love adding it to a space. Styling shelves can be a task in itself so I thought I would share a few of my favorite tips!

1. Create balance with various heights
2. Incorporate different materials, textures, and finishes
3. Use books as anchor pieces around the shelves (we mostly get our books from thrift stores to find these!) 

I hope this helps so you don’t have to have anymore stress when it comes to designing and decorating! What do you add to your shelves? Let me know! 🫶🏻 #EuropeanMountain

Creating a beautiful home involves making a lot of decisions, both big and small… 💭⭐️🤍 #europeanmountain 

Even the little things, like how high to place a wall sconce, where to end a backsplash, which style of door to choose, the size of the windows, and how to mix different metals, can make a big difference in how a room looks and feels. That's why many people who hire a designer feel grateful for the help. A good designer can handle these difficult decisions with ease and make sure that every part of the home works together perfectly.
